From 62fb64b23331d4f879caaf0ac8f9cde30f45cccf Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Philippe Gerum <rpm@xenomai.org>
Date: Thu, 6 Apr 2017 17:52:17 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 051/174] irq_pipeline: add proxy tick device

The proxy tick device is a synthetic clock event device interposing on
the real clock event device which honors the clock_event_device
interface.

Once the proxy is installed, an oob layer can take control of the
underlying real device for carrying out its own timing duties,
handling the timing requests from the in-band kernel sent to the proxy
device too.

Signed-off-by: Philippe Gerum <rpm@xenomai.org>
